reviews_data.review_text: Awesome tasting food and drinks, well priced!
Great food!
Cute atmosphere, nice service and decent food. A bit pricey though especially considering the portions

This is a cute neighborhood outpost of the Salted Melon “chain” (there are now 3 locations, I think?) it’s nice because it has parking. There is inside and outside seating. You order at the counter and then get a number for your table. Whatever finish is on the tables makes it sticky, so it doesn’t necessarily feel clean, even though you JUST watched someone clean the table. The number of choices is manageable. We went for brunch, so there were a handful of choices. My strawberry fields forever iced coffee was amazing. I could probably drink those non stop. The bandito (breakfast) burrito was good. It was egg heavy, but I liked that it included tater tots. The avocado toast was pretty plain and seemed expensive for what you got. The notorious BEC was pretty standard. The plating was very basic for all- nothing fancy. The silverware was nice and heavy. The water:ice machine was kind of cool - you could pick just ice, just water, or both! The decor was cute inside and the people working there were nice. Our orders came out sporadically, even though we ordered at the same time. They did a brisk business with lots of people inside and out enjoying a meal. Overall, I would go again- it’s convenient and quick, but very basic.

Went last Sunday (6/15/25), got a Miss Melon smoothie, it was not blended correctly and had chunks of watermelon in it still. We approached the counter and Lilly (who we found out later was the manager) seemed annoyed that we said something about the smoothie not being blended completely.
She took the smoothie and poured it back into the blender and “blended” it again, only for it to result in the same chunks. Lilly seemed to not only not care that there were chunks still, she didn’t care that a portion of the smoothie was left in the blender still, resulting in less being poured back into the cup.

I sent an email to link provided on the website, hoping to hear back from them and have a resolution and nothing has come from that.
It really seems that not only does the management at the shop have no care to resolve issues, it seems like that’s the overall attitude of the company.
The bacon, egg, & cheese bagel was HUGE! It was absolutely delicious and I look forward to trying more menu items. Such a cute spot and the service is outstanding.

Farmhouse breakfast was ok for the price.
I liked my Mocha, it was really good.
Maybe will be coming back to try lunch menu in future.
Food was cold when received
Really bad chicken Caesar wrap, it was super bland and dry.
We had an amazing brunch today at Salted Melon, not only because of the delicious food and drinks, but because of the phenomenal service from our sever Jonah. He was so thorough, attentive, and kind!

Hi! I absolutely loved eating here. The staff is so friendly and welcoming, especially Anna! She gives the best recommendations and is super nice throughout the ordering experience. I really enjoyed my food!

I had the pleasure of visiting this cute spot while traveling to the Charlotte area. The “Market Chop” salad with the brûléed goat cheese may be my new favorite meal! As a fan of goat cheese on salads and other dishes, it’s hard to find at many restaurants. I love that they offer it and then to prep it like they do…oh my! So yummy! (Seriously, can you make that an appetizer? 🙃)
The young ladies who helped me with the menu and offered suggestions were absolutely delightful. The place was clean and the atmosphere was friendly. Definitely worth visiting anytime I’m in town!

Females who work there are anti male and accuse male workers of things they didn't do..don't go there
.

Casual, clean, and great food.

Salmon poke was really good.
Diverse menu that has something for everyone. Food was fresh and ambiance and was nice; Great addition to the area!
Tried this recently when I found that Panera down the street had closed, and it did not disappoint. Great option for lunch! Would be 5-stars except it’s a bit pricey. Very quick service!
Thankful to have such a flavorful and healthy quick to-go or eat in spot like Salted Melon. To be in such a large city the options are few when it comes to clean eating as well as tasty!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: A Chicken Caprese and a Watermelon Salad

reviews_data.review_text: I’ve been to the SouthEnd location & so was excited to try this one. Such a cute vibe! While it was busy, we didn’t wait long at the counter to order & easily found a table. The service was good, friendly & fast. I had the truffle fries & the Summer Salmon bowl, but were delicious! Would be great for a quick lunch!
Food is unique and very good.  A lot of vegetarian options.
Great lunch place. I see lots of business people here

The place looks great! The service even better :) But this food is for someone that thinks pepper is spicy. All the food is extremely bland and with the $16 price tag my food came with I expected a lot more. How they managed to get a second location is a mystery, tons of better eats in Charlotte. My advice would be to actually focus on the food instead of an Instagram worthy dining room.

Had the street car bowl. It was rice, tomatos, corn, cilantro and peppers with steak, it was very chewy. Not a lot of flavor. Not impressed. It was $17 and I'm extremely disappointed. My daughter got the chicken Caesar wrap and the chicken was very dry and chewy and not cut up very well. Her wrap was $13.50. Not much flavor. She got a sprite that was $3.50 and a tiny iced cookie that was mediocre at best for $5.00.   We ended up throwing the meals in the trash. Definitely not going to return. Not good.

My wife and I visited this new location of Salted Melon and enjoyed it very much. Great food, location, staff was friendly, very clean here and the decor was very nice inside. This was a former Hubee Dee’s chicken restaurant and they turned it very nice inside here.

This salted melon is different from the Southend location so there’s not a market inside like you would see at Southend, but you have Harris Teeter right down the road so it’s not a big deal for a market here.

The food was amazing along with the iced lattes we got! We definitely enjoyed this location a lot and will return back for sure.

As an FYI, parking does get super busy here so be aware of that when you come at prime time lunch or breakfast time. Make sure you also download their app so you can earn reward points! It definitely will help you in the long run!
Excellent restaurant, nice atmosphere. The employees are very attentive. very good reputation employees. Kitchen employees are always attentive to orders and everyone leaves on time.
